mkdir -p ~/docker/ai-home/homeassistant-data/.ssh
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 ...
🟡 MINOR ISSUES (Affects clarity, efficiency, or operational risk)

1. Local Network Lockout Risk (Fail2ban)

Location: Phase 4 (Step 5) – Fail2ban Configuration

Issue: The MaxAuthTries 3 SSH rule combined with fail2ban creates a strict perimeter. If the user fat-fingers their SSH key passphrase or attempts to log in from a new local laptop without copying the key first, their local LAN IP will be banned, severing all SSH access to their own server.

Fix / Resolution: It is highly recommended to whitelist local subnets in /etc/fail2ban/jail.local to prevent accidental lockouts from the local network:

code
Ini
